<rate>5< /rate>< text>
Awesome spot. I order a couple of Steak n Shrimp tacos and they were ready in less than 10 minutes. Very filling (lots of meat) and delicious with avocado, cabbage, onions, cilantro and sauce! Came with a large side of chips and salsa, good deal. I recommend this spot for taco cravings and I will return.</text>

<review>I came here today for my birthday dinner since I wanted to try a new place and I has been waiting to try the food here. I tried to online through the website but it said it wasn't accepting any orders so I called them instead. They said they are open for phone orders but I asked if I could place my order through yelp and they said yes. So I got the Turf Burrito with Carne Asasa Steak with no rice or beans and I asked for extra tomato and cilantro. My food was ready within like 15 minutes compared to yelp telling me it would he ready in 20-40 minutes. I thought their burritos was very good, all that was missing for me was some pico de gallo and hot sauces. I think they want you to basically use the sauce that comes with the burrito which is their Chipotle Sauce. I wasn't sure if I had to ask for pico de gallo or hot sauce when I pick up my order but I'll try next time.< /review>< Pictures>

<name>Edward Rogers<//name>< date>
1601069862026< /date>
<rating>3<//rating>< text>
I showed up at a very slow 1pm for lunch. Never been here before so i always go to a new place with an open mind.

Fish Tacos: the meat was overcooked, and there was just way too much cabbage/slaw. No fish flavor at all.

Asada Tacos: The meat should have a very simple savory flavor and the condiments should do the talking. I feel like meat was over spiced, which in turn changed the flavor of the salsa. Just not my cup of tea.

I don't think the owners really focused on creating a good flavor spectrum. They should really consider hiring a cook that really knows Mexican food.

I don't want this to be a hate post, or a negative feedback. Hopefully it is seen as constructive criticism.</text>

< review>
Stumbled upon this tiny taco joint while driving up the street. Andy (the owner) was outside & greeted us with a huge smile. We ordered the steak & shrimp tacos and chicken turf torta. Both were delicious! The tacos were equal parts citrusy, tangy & sweet and the cabbage slaw gave it the perfect crunch with each bite. This is a great neighborhood taco joint to support with the best customer service and even better food!< /review>

<Rating>4< /Rating>< text>
Secret Trail is a great place to get local craft beer. They brew on site and have an awesome hiking/outdoorsy feel to the place. Honestly it's a really great mix up to getting locally Crafted beer and not having to face the crowded taproom at Sierra Nevada.(I love Sierra Nevada too) They have snacks, chips, trail mix, popcorn and they often have a food truck outside too. But it would be nice to see them have a variety of food trucks or be able to make small plates in house. Overall so excited that this place opened. They aren't open weekends or Monday and Tuesday to the public.</text>

< Review>
I wasn't aware that the "industrial heart" of Chico held such treasure, but my first inkling came when, thirsty from a trying day, largely spent considering how the day might be better spent, I slunk into my previously favorite watering hole (whose name shall not be uttered here out of respect for the dead) but after settling into a dark corner, I was informed that my standby Porter had just foamed it's last -- the keg was dry ...... but "you might wanna try the Trail of Darkness, it's pretty good". Initially shaken by the sudden and unexpected loss of my dearest libation,  a multitude of emotions swept over me; disappointment, anger, even a sense of betrayal rose like gore in my throat, rendering it difficult to croak out a numb "okay, I'll try one". I remained slumped and brooding until a glass was slid under my nose -- and here I have to admit that the aroma that wafted up from it's foamy brow was not off-putting at all. In fact it was perfect! I raised the glass to my lips and was once again not disappointed. It was in a word ... er, make that words, the best Porter of my experience. Slamming it down, my fingers frantically flew over my phone in an effort to ferret out the source of this wonder, and lo, Secret Trail was just mere blocks away -- how had I squandered so much time in ignorance of it's existence? But then, what's the use of mourning the past, it's the present  that we live in, and I pledged to make up for lost time -- and I have! Simply put, there's not a bad brew in the house (rare for a micro brewery) and many offerings are in the "best of class" category. In addition to the Trail of Darkness the, Hundinator, Hands Across The Pond, the Barrel Aged Baltic Porter, and Nitro Baltic Porter -- respectively, a Porter, Doppelbock, Barleywine, and two variations on their Baltic Porter are all best of class offerings. So if you like beer of unstinting quality, and bearded men, this is the place for you!< /Review>

<user_id>107614169792016106425<//user_id><time>1511115187632<//time><GmapID>0x808326243078ada3:0x74b3fc378eba7b9f<//GmapID><Response>{'time': 1515548056987, 'text': 'Thank you for your kind review Giovanni!'}< /Response><rate>5< /rate><Review>I highly recommend checking this place out. We heard about the grand opening from a friend and swung by before going downtown. The place looks and feels amazing with its Chico-esque decoration. The staff were really friendly even though I'm sure they had had a long day with the opening and must have been tired by the time we got there. We got a flight of beers for $10 and the pour of each was a great amount for the price you pay. I also bought a patch and a glass before leaving. I really love the quote they have on their glasses "Live and Drink off the Beaten Path" which definitely speaks to my Chico side! As I'm not a beer connoisseur, I can't speak to that but I can say all their options were great. I prefer lighter beers so their Hazy Trail was my favorite but I was surprised at the taste of their darks as they were great as well. This feels like it will be a great place to hangout at after work or simply meet up with some friends on the weekend. While they don't have food options aside from snacks, the food trucks do setup outside so you can call and see what options they have the day off. Overall, you need to try this place!<//Review></record></dataset><record>

<review>I have a start up and have been renting space here since Feb. Great place, great people, great service with a start-up focus. The offices have a great view of the bay, and the benefits/perks are real and worth it. IE Zoom Conference and AWS have helped us get started. There are several mentors that you can network with and it's good to collaborate or get advice from a few of the other founders. Highly recommend!

- Edit 5 months later. We were accepted into another incubator and we have bounced around between several office spaces in the area. In my opinion, being in an office space that is as nice as OneValley, and with their focus on StartUps, their is not a better space. What I've found is that many office spaces are rundown old buildings with big names, uncomfortable desks with high prices, or is hosted by an incubator that is not a tech focus. OneValley has a good combination that will make your team feel good about where they work, with all the parking space you could want, and the staff that you will love.<//review><pictures>None<//pictures><response>{'time': 1600968153968, 'text': 'Thank you Lowel we appreciate your feedback, and the San Mateo team absolutely love getting to see you each day. <review>Beware, SCAM! In their Passport program they offer you huge discounts from their partners like Amazon, Azure, Hubspot etc. They would charge you for that $500/year. After paying this amount you will learn that all they do is to redirect you to their partners websites (using affiliate links). For example, they offer on their website $10,000 AWS credits. You need to pay $500 to redeem it. You pay, you click redeem, and you end up on aws.amazon.com website. Keep away!< /review></record>

< name>

< UserId.>
109074299801961605802<//UserId.>
<gmapID>0x808f80b66d881779:0x7e71647aea7ba838<//gmapID>< pics>
None</pics>
<date>1439153524062< /date><Review>Chilli Padi serves excellent Malaysian cuisine, in a sea of Chinese restaurants in Oakland Chinatown. This place looks (and is) new compared to almost every other restaurant in Oakland Chinatown (except maybe Shooting Star Cafe on Webster St). Inside, the restaurant is very clean and looks new (because it is) and the atmosphere consists of several muted TVs usually showing HGTV/Food Network. I can safely assume Chilli Padi will stay in business for a while, as the food and service is top-notch. Just about every single dish here is fantastic, and the service is prompt--the servers are quick to take note of water glasses that need refilling, and if you need to box leftovers to take home (which they do for you). The manager is a very friendly dude, and can be helpful if you need help deciding what to try.

As for the food itself...if you're wondering what Malaysian food is, it's basically a mix of Thai, Chinese and Indian cuisine with more of a flavorful (and sometimes spicy) side. My favorite dishes here are mango chicken, string beans belachan and singapore fried vermicelli. Note that while most dishes are designed to be ordered and eaten family-style (e.g. mango chicken is not a 'complete meal/comes with rice' dish, you'd have to order the rice separately), many fried rice and noodles dishes are pretty complete meals on their own as they often come with multiple meal ingredients such as chicken, shrimp and a variety of vegetables. They serve free dessert soup after your meal, usually a sweet tapioca and potato soup or my personal favorite, sweet black rice soup. Note that if you want a less spicy version of a dish, you can tell the waiter or waitress taking your order and they will ask the cooks to tone the spice down.

Overall, an excellent restaurant in a rather run-down looking location (for now, at least). I say, at least give it a try if you're unsure--you probably won't regret it!</Review><Response>None</Response></record>
</dataset><record>

5< /rating>

< text>
From the beginning (within days of being hit by another driver), while recovering from a major concussion with loss of memory, Mickey Fine's staff guided me through rough waters. His investigator arranged all initial meetings and paperwork. His staff, specifically Mrs. McHugh were phenomenal about responding to all questions promptly. I have never waited a full day for a reply to any question. They did not fit the perception I had of a lawyer at any point. I assumed it would be difficult to get their time and attention without appointments, but they even went as far as to invite me to the offices on multiple occasions so that I could see their team working for me and not just be a name on an email string.

Even with partial amnesia for two weeks after the accident and long term degradation of memory processing, Mr. Fine's offices were having a hard time displaying to the insurance companies that I had a significant injury.  They never waivered from aggressively and diligently representing me.  They took the load of pursuing what I could not have on my behalf, and remained steadfast for nearly 2 years until it was resolved and settled. I would have given up doing it myself in the first year, I just have never seen such dedicated focus...it was as if I was treated as their only client, even though they had plenty of clients that they were representing.

I have and will continue to recommend Mickey Fine and his staff to anyone who is in need of representation.  They are a top notch organization.

Neil<//text>

I went two different times with coworkers within the same month. I raved about the food to my coworkers telling them I hadn't eaten there in months but I know it was good food. The 1st time when the server brought our food they didnt have my order correct at all. By the time I got my food my friends were just about done. My order STILL wasnt right they didn't give me the eggs that I asked for and they didn't give me the side of tortillas. I didn't complain I just took it to go. The 2nd time I took a coworker for breakfast. I told her the food was very good! But while I was eating I found a hair under my eggs and rice! Grossed me out! As I was pulling the hair from under my food a server walked by and I showed him. He apologized and said he can make me a new one or give me a refund. I said no I want the food I am hungry. It was about 15-20 minutes later I went to use the restroom and seen the server with other employees sitting at a booth. I went to the cashier and asked where my food was and she had no idea that I needed my food still. Since my friend was practically done I asked for a refund. I was so upset! I did eat the free chips and salsa which were very good! When a pregnant woman is hungry she Is Hungry! Sorry that I left a 1 rating the food is really good. But I just got screwed over twice! <rate>2<//rate>< review>
Went there today for father's day and it was a mess. I truly regret dropping $100 on such bad customer service. My group consisted of four people. Me, my wife, mom and dad. To start the food took way too long. I had ordered two shrimp cocktails, which you would think those would have been delivered first maybe about 15 minutes into the order. Anyways, my dad gets his food first 30 minutes after ordering. Then about ten minutes later my wife and I get our food and about ten more minutes my mom.  It took about 50 minutes before my mom could get a plate of menudo. Then to top it off my wife's order was wrong so we had to send it back. My food came with tortillas which I never got and quite frankly we had been waiting so long for our food that we got filled with the tortilla chips and salsa.

Now it was busy so I have some sympathy but not much. The bottom line is we are still customers and that should not be an excuse. I've been there once on a regular business day and the service was ok not great ok. So like I said I know the potential for them to give great customer service is their. I feel that management should do a better job of preparing for busy days like this ensuring that they have enough staff and watching everything carefully so that it does not take up to 50 minutes to have someone's food delivered.</review>
